    "title" : "A way to use variable without reassigning inside if block",
    "body" : "<pre><code>int min = nums[i + 1];  //&lt;-- initial declaration       \nfor (int j = i+2; j &lt;nums.length ; j++) {\n    if (nums[j] &lt; min) {\n        min = nums[j]; //&lt;--reassigning                   \n    }\n}\nif (min &lt; current) {\n       swap(nums, i, minIndex);\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>When I reassign variable &quot;<strong>min</strong>&quot;, IntelliJ Idea gives me &quot;<strong>Reassigned local variable</strong>&quot; warning and underlines it. If I change the variable name, I can't use it inside if block underneath because it goes out of scope. Is there a better way? (not reassigning and ability to use min inside if block)</p>\n",
