    "question_id" : 79552554,
    "body" : "<p>If you are using Java 8+, you can use the Stream API to get the min value. Here\n<a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/17/docs/api/java.base/java/util/Arrays.html#stream(int%5B%5D,int,int)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Arrays.stream(int[] array, int startInclusive, int endExclusive)</code></a> creates a stream from the array, starting from element at <code>i+1</code> to the end:</p>\n<pre><code>int min = Arrays.stream(nums, i + 1, nums.length)\n                .min()\n                .orElse(nums[i + 1]);\n</code></pre>\n",
